The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Sistema set for Calcutta foray
                                                                                                               Sistema set for Calcutta foray
          A STAFF REPORTER                                              RISING NETWORK      
	Calcutta, April 26: Sistema Shyam Teleservices is ready to roll out its CDMA services in Calcutta next month.         
	The company will launch its services in the other parts of Bengal by mid-June and in Bihar by July.         
	Sistema Shyam  a 74:26 joint venture between Shyam Group and Russias Sistema  has tied up with Mobile TeleSystems to offer the latters MTS brand in India.        
	The MTS brand of mobile services would be launched in Calcutta next month followed by other eastern states, Alexander Chinyaev, Sistemas chief representative in India, said.         
	Sistema Shyam launched its mobile service in October in Rajasthan. The company tied up with Mobile TeleSystems of Russia in December.        
	We currently offer mobile services in Tamil Nadu, Rajasthan and Kerala and within six months of operations, our subscriber base has reached very close to 1 million, Chinyaev had said on the sidelines of an interactive session at the Merchants Chamber of Commerce earlier.        
	As an introductory offer, the service provider will offer free talk time to its subscribers.         
	Sistema Shyam Teleservices is also planning to complete its all-India launch by the third quarter of 2010.        
	Headquartered in Gurgaon, the company has the licences and spectrum to provide mobile telephony services in all the 22 circles in the country.                                                                                                                                        
